records.Title: Canada Pension Plan (CPP)
records.Summary: The Canada Pension Plan (CPP) retirement pension is a monthly, taxable benefit that replaces part of your income when you retire. If you qualify, you’ll receive the CPP retirement pension for the rest of your life.

records.Title: How to submit request to replace solar panel
records.Summary: If you've noticed that one or more of your solar panels are damaged, malfunctioning, or not performing as expected, it may be time to submit a request to replace them. Replacing faulty solar panels is essential to maintain the efficiency and effectiveness of your solar energy system. In this guide, we'll walk you through the process of submitting a request to replace a solar panel, ensuring a smooth and hassle-free experience.

records.Title: How do I reset my solar panel system?
records.Summary: Resetting your solar panel system may become necessary in certain situations, such as troubleshooting performance issues or addressing errors in system operation. While the process may vary depending on the type of system you have, this guide provides a general overview of how to reset a solar panel system safely and effectively.

records.Title: How to install your new solar panel
records.Summary: Installing solar panels is a rewarding project that can help you reduce your carbon footprint and save on electricity bills. While the process may seem daunting, with proper planning and execution, you can successfully install solar panels on your property. This guide provides step-by-step instructions to help you navigate the installation process and harness the power of solar energy.

records.Title: Solar panel isn't producing much electricity
records.Summary: Most energy production issues are caused by system components other than the panels, such as the solar inverter, charge controller, wiring or batteries.

records.Title: Condensation inside solar panel
records.Summary: Condensation in solar panels results from temperature variations, affecting efficiency and durability. Solutions encompass ventilation, humidity control, sealing, maintenance, panel tilt, and coatings, ensuring consistent solar energy performance over time.

records.Title: Cracked wind turbine blade
records.Summary: Our wind turbine blades are designed to be replaced individually so there is no need to purchase an entire blade assembly. You can even 3D print your own replacement with our downloadable models on our website.

records.Title: Loud noise coming from wind turbine
records.Summary: If your wind turbine is making a loud grinding or squealing noise, it probably has a broken rotator seal and potentially gear damage if it has been happening for a while.

records.Title: Wind turbine rotor stopped turning
records.Summary: Wind turbine rotor stoppage reasons include wind conditions, mechanical/electrical problems, blade damage, icing, environment, or system issues. Maintenance, quick troubleshooting, and operational awareness are vital for consistent energy generation.
